    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="poem">
                <head type="title"><handShift new="#HANDJR1826-27" script="print" medium="pencil"/>Title of Poem</head>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l>I weary for the torrent leaping</l>
                    <l>from off the <del rend="strikethrough">mountain</del><add place="below"><space quantity="14" unit="chars"/>scars rough</add> crest</l>
                    <l>My muse is on the mountain sleeping</l>
                    <l>My harp is sunk to rest</l>
                </lg>
                <lg>
                    <l>I weary for the fountain foaming</l>
                    <l>for shady holme &#x0026; hill</l>
                    <l>My mind is on the mountain roaming</l>
                    <l>My lyres voice is still.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg>
                    <l>I weary for the woodland brook</l>
                    <l>that wanders through the vale</l>
                    <l><del rend="strikethrough">That</del> I weary for the heights that look</l>
                    <l>adown upon the dale</l>
                </lg>
                <lg>
                    <l>The crags are lone on Conistone</l>
                    <l>&#x0026; <del rend="strikethrough"><geogName corresp="#GLARAMARA">Glaramara</geogName>s</del> <geogName corresp="#LOWESWATER">Loweswater</geogName>s dell</l>
                    <l>And dreary on the mighty one</l>
                    <l>The cloud enwreathed Scawfell</l>
                </lg>
                <lg>
                    <l>Oh what although the crags be stern</l>
                    <l>Their craggy peaks that sever</l>
                    <l>Fresh flies the breeze on mountain fern</l>
                    <l>And free on mountain heather</l>
                </lg>
                <lg>
                    <l>There is a<del type="strikethrough"><unclear resp="#DCH">t</unclear></del> thrill of strange delight</l>
                    <l>That passeth quivering oer me</l>
                    <l>When blue hills fade upon the sight</l>
                    <l>Like summer clouds before</l>
                </lg>
                <pb/>
                <lg>
                    <l>Tis transient, as the <del rend="strikethrough">winters</del><add place="below"><space quantity="23" unit="chars"/>snowy</add> drift</l>
                    <l>That passeth away</l>
                    <l>Tis like the blush of morn that swift</l>
                    <l>Doth melt into the day</l>
                </lg>
                <lg>
                    <l>I long to tread the mountain head</l>
                    <l>Above the valley swelling</l>
                    <l>I long to feel the breeze fled</l>
                    <l>From grey &#x0026; gaunt <geogName corresp="#HELVELLYN">Helvellyn</geogName>.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg>
                    <l>I love the eddying circling sweep</l>
                    <l>The mantling and the foam</l>
                    <l>Of murmuring waters dark and deep</l>
                    <l>Amid the valleys lone</l>
                </lg>
                <lg>
                    <l>It is a terror, yet tis sweet</l>
                    <l>Upon some broken brow</l>
                    <l>To look upon the distant sweep</l>
                    <l>Of <del corresp="strikethrough">lake or</del>> ocean spread below</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
            
